<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-03-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-03-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="536" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d536">
                        <head>536. Telegram 4 from Geneva to Warsaw<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d536fn1">Source: Department of State, Central Files,
                                611.93/3–1356. Secret. Repeated for information to the Department of
                                State as telegram 1632.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName>Geneva</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-03-13">March 13, 1956, 10
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <pb facs="d536-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d536-1"/>
                        <p>4. From <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                        <p><persName corresp="#p_WP_1">Wang</persName> called tonight asking
                            postpone our next meeting to March 22 stating it necessary he leave here
                            March 14 for Warsaw “on urgent business”.</p>
                        <p>In order assist in assessing this move would appreciate any information
                            you can discreetly obtain as to what if any “urgent business” might
                            require his presence there.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_GFC_1"><hi rend="strong">Gowen</hi></persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>